text:
Travelling Library: A view of the library truck operated by the Extension Division of the New York Public Library as it stopped on Wallace Avenue, near Astor Avenue to serve the young readers of the neighborhood. This is a set of three views taken the same day, at the same location.

May 11, 1938.

P. L. Sperr
title: Travelling Library - Bronx.
